invalid type: string "4. Parallel Vectors ‚Äď Vectors acting in the same or opposite directions. \nAddition of Vectors \nVectors can be added using: \n‚ÄĘ Triangle Law of Vector Addition \n‚ÄĘ Parallelogram Law of Vector Addition \nIf two vectors act at an angle to each other, their resultant can be found using: \nR=\\sqrt{A^2+B^2+2AB\\cos\\theta} \nwhere: \n‚ÄĘ (R) = resultant vector \nˇˇˇˇˇˇˇˇˇˇ